so...you may have guessed it by now, but i'm wierd. really wired. the kind of wierd where you don't know if i'm increadibly awsome or should be locked up in a padded room. well, i'll tell you...both. (you know, it would be AWSOME to have a room padded all around in rubber that you could bounce on...) and to get BACK to the point... my name is nicole. i am 19 (and a half). i live in hell, i mean with my aunt and uncle. slowly losing my sanity. i have a boyfriend of 2 and a half years. his name is justin. we are sickeningly sweet togeather. i don't like to use caps. i can't spell that well on the first try. i'm afriad of bees and chickens and jello and being in bathrooms with no lights on and mirrors freak me out. i have a highly active imagination and am VERY easily amused. i talk alot. i am loud and quite. i'm quite the oxymoron. i tend to obsess about really awsome things easily. i love the color purple and wednesday (the day of the week) and the #5 and fruit and being warm and laughing and shiny things and spelling things like color with a "u" (but i restrain myself). i have a morbid and sometimes distrubing mind that, even though i seen all chipper and hyper and hippie-ish, dark things apeal to me. yay for personal tragedy!

i was born in lajolla (la hoya) california when i was an infant, lived in ocean beaches for a while (or so i'm told), moved a lot (to places like hawaii and oregon and hawaii and oregon and hawaii and washinton and oregon and san diego and oregon and washington and texas and washington and washington and now here i am, in wasington (lynnwood/edmonds). i now live right behind EDCC. isn't that special? 

i plan to do something with my life. that's about as much of the details as i've worked out for now. i'm going to finish my AA in a year (it will have only taken me 3 years to do it. okay, so my first year here was badly spent...so?) i like to write, but my muse seems to be sorrow and my unhappyness, and for the first time in a while, i'm pretty happy (for the most part). i'm mostly a poet i guess. right now i'm selling sunglasses. in the mall. in seattle. in the winter. oh, my job has such a purpose, let me tell you. 

right now i'm reading (aside from frankenstein) a book i found outside half price books for a dollar called "dark to mortal eyes" by some guy i've never heard of and i as of yet still couldn't really tell you what it's about, but the title was gripping and the picture was really cool. i have phases where i become obsessed with an author. right now it's orson scott card. i've already put a list of some of my authors and stuff up. i love joss whedon and neil gaiman. i also love anne mccaffrey's dragon riders of pern series, as lame as her stuff can be. movies, i like: serinity (of course); the princess bride; powder; stigmata; leathal weapon; oldschool starwars and #3; those 80's movies like pretty in pink and the breakfast club and the lost boys and the fantasy movies like labyrinth and the last unicorn and the dark crystal; superhero/comic book movies like the supermans, the four batmans started by tim burtons origional one (not the newest one though), and constintine. NOT daredevil or hulk or the LXG, those make me sad. 

i should probably end this now. wow, but it's long. i like to do this though, write my bio. i don't know why really. oh well. later all. i'm sure if you can't place me now, you'll be on the look out for me on wednesday, and i'm not hard to miss.

~peace
</lj-cut>

THE LIVING EARTH "Viewed from the distance of the moon, the astonishing thing about the earth, catching the breath, is that it is alive. The photographs show the dry, pounded surface of the moon in the foreground, dry as an old bone. Aloft, floating free beneath the moist, gleaming, membrane of bright blue sky, is the rising earth, the only exuberant thing in this part of the cosmos. If you could look long enough, you would see the swirling of the great drifts of white cloud, covering and uncovering the half-hidden masses of land. If you had been looking for a very long, geologic time, you could have seen the continents themselves in motion, drifting apart on their crustal plates, held afloat by the fire beneath. It has the organized, self-contained look of a live creature, full of information, marvelously skilled in handling the sun." ~Lewis Thomas the gaia hypothesis

LJ Interests meme results

  1. barenaked ladies:
    okay, BNL kicks so much ass. they are canadian and weird, and i met them (granted, i was asleep and it was a dream, but ed sang right to me, but he doesn't give dream autographs, and jim couldn't be there. i was sad.).
  2. colors:
    why would colors need to be explained? they are interesting and give variety. all of them. i love the spectrum. the rainbow and everything in between. black isn't really a color (it's an absence of light), but i like it too.
  3. diversity:
    if everything was the same the world would die of boredom.
  4. friends:
    friends make living worthwhile. if you don't have friends of all degrees (from uber-best brainwave sharing friendships to random aquaintences you run into and chat with) then what would be the point of ever leaving the house?
  5. humor:
    if i couldn't laught at myself (and with those who laugh at me), then nothing would be fun. try to find the humor in any situation, even if you keep it to yourself. it makes things bareable.
  6. love:
    if you don't love others, no one will love you.
  7. music:
    i couldn't live with out music. it fits any mood. it changes the mood you're in. and it can portray very profound ideas.
  8. pretty days:
    come on! i need to explain why i like pretty days? although, i can find any day pretty.
  9. sci-fi/fantasy:
    hell the freak yeah! sci-fi/fantasy is awsome. though i do have expectations. i'm not all that tolerant towards really stupid sci-fi/fantasy. especially fantasy. stupid sci-fi is doable in small doses at the proper time.

    neil gaiman is brilliant, and i love his idea of the personification of basic principles and ideas throught time (destiny, death, dream, desire, dispare, destruction, delight/delerium)<--from memory. and they are just freaking cool on they're own.

i'm killing time online cause i want to make absolutely POSITIVE that they are very much unconscious when i get back. i do not want to speak to/with either of them right now. especially my aunt. my god people! today i got slightly reprimanded by my aunt for not eating meat. she said things like i do it because i'm a teenager (19, wtf?) and do it to be different and unique. like i'm the ONLY person in the ENTIRE world who doesn't eat meat. see, my friend (yes, i have friends) was over yesterday and she's vegan and so my aunt brought her into it to saying something like 'when she's 25 she still won't be doing that' or something (not an exact quote). then i turned the conversation back on me, cause it's not right for my aunt to be ticked with me and bring someone else into it as an example for how i do wrong. and she was talking about how the world has been doing fine as it is for the past bla bla bla bla bla and now i'm trying to change the world cause i "saw the light" or whatever (sarcastically said of course) about eating meat. i don't try to change anyone or their eating habits. i respect everyone's differences and would like them to respect mine. but she was like 'since your non-meat eating isn't a moral or religious issue (and here she referenced catholicism and lent) then you should make a personal sacrifice at times when you would be in danger of insulting you hostess.' a particular example is this chili that was for dinner last night, and i could have eaten it, because there wasn't MUCH turkey and i wouldn't have been able to TASTE it, so there souldn't have been a problem with it. and she basically said that vegetarianism is "ridiculous" (she actually said that, but i'm not sure if she meant just my case, or in general). i have my reasons. just because they don't seem like the RIGHT reasons to some people, doesn't mean that i should go eat a large steak or something. it just pissed me off that she was trying to turn me away from not eating meat. then she had to mention how my eating habits aren't exactly healthy. which pisses me off because i know i'm not doing very well in eating right, but when i have to live THERE and deal with all their various crap, i end up eating and watching a lot of tv because it's the only thing i can feel good doing in that house. so far she's made me feel guilty about spending too much time in my room, because i'm not being "social". i just plain don't WANT to spend too much time upstairs around them, cause they just talk at me. there was a recent "confrontation" about music, don't even get me to do. and i freaking do them. as it is so nicely phrased, "home is where the heart is" and if that is true, then my home is with justin, and the PLACE that i still consider to be my home is with seattle BUNCHES better). i live in a cavelike basement room in my aunts house in which i feel like a guest who has overstayed her welcome. i wish i could get my act together and get my ass out, but is wrong with me lately? i've been reading around, in various journals and such, and i've come to the conclusion (which has been fermenting in my mind for a while now) that i've just become a superficial and childish whatever. i've not really written anything of substance (or really anything at all) since early this year. since then i've been relatively happy, and i guess my only muse is depression. happy or numb. both i think. a little more numb tho. i haven't truly written anything in about a year and a half... it's not just the writing though. it's everything. everything i talk about. most of what i think. okay, not what i think. i still have some thoughts with some depth to them. i just don't communicate them really in any way. i don't know. i spend most of my energies on school and work (and bitching oh so much on the continuing downward spiral of my god forsaken job) til it eats most of me up, then with what i have left i spend on justin and waste the extras on retarded tv (which, to be perfectly honest, i think is stupid and pointless and i didn't really miss much when i over reacted and went insane about a year ago and stuck mine in my closet) which i assume i use primarily as an escape because living where i live is slowly draining me of everything that i am with all the mind games and the feelings of guilt and how i'm probably disappointing them, even though i told myself that i don't care what they think, it's a lie cause i do. i always care. what everyone thinks because i just don't want to disappoint them. and they think i'm such a shallow and immature and selfish person because i don't feel that i can be myself around them, or even in that house ate all really, and i just REALLY don't like them at all and want to spend as much time away from them as possible. then my aunt gives me shit about spending a lot of time in my room, so now i barely go in there and i feel weird when i am in there alone. i used to love being in my room alone. that's where i would write and just do whatever. that was with my stepmom and my actual FAMILY and i felt myself there. and i miss it so much. and so i just stay up until i'm exhausted and crash in my bed, then wake at the last minute and rush off to school. i loath going upstairs in the morning. i KNOW they're there, and i just DON"T want to interact with them. and so i get shit about when i wake up. and they just dont' get that i behave how i do because i can't stand them, and i do what i can to keep what sanity there still is in me. i always feel like the errant child, and they feel this need to parent me. i haven't really been parented since i was 8. there was the brief time when i was taken in my my friends family, but aside from that i looked out for myself. i fed myself, i did my laundry, i gathered what advice i needed from my dad and his friends and good tv and books and teachers and molded it all into myself. i extrapolated what i could from everywhere and taught myself about the birds and the bees and the feminine "stuff" (except for shaving, which i got a few tips from my best friend's mom and my dad's at the time girlfriend), and i made some pretty good decisions about life and choices i should make, all things considered. but they don't consider any of that. they look at me and see a poor little orphan girl who lost her mom young and didn't have that figure to model myself after, and who's dad did the best he could but to them i don't think it was good enough, who doesn't seem to take shit seriously and who is sarcastic and immature and should be treated like she's 14 and checked up on to see if she's at work and can't be trusted to take care of her own education and is horrible and sinful and stupid for sleeping with her boyfriend before marriage (hypocrites, that's all i have to say on that matter) and everything else unacceptable to them. they don't see that i bust my ass for my job and my school and my boyfriend and to try to make them like me even though i really don't what to care what they think and that i stayed away from all the bad shit that i could have gotten into because of my rocky childhood, and i'm finishing school when i could have just given up and that i have high moral ideas about love and sex and i would never have done anything if it hadn't felt right (because i hadn't before). i'm not like them in their thoughts and beliefs so i need to be trained to become the next jennifer, popping out millions of babies like a good catholic wife with issues with her mother. they see my childhood and how i was raised and it's not how they would have done it, so it's wrong and must be amended. never mind that i was happy. never mind that i look back on it with nothing but fondness. i was raised by artistic parents with hippie-ish qualities in a semi-nomadic and kinda poor lifestyle and i wouldn't trade that for all the middle class surburban houses with the picket fances and soccer practice and minivans and cubicle clone parents. i've just so lost touch. i have thoughts and ideas and beliefs but i have no knowledge to back it up. and i have no drive to find that knowledge. i'm just numb and coocooning myself in my own little bubble. the rare bursts of reality that find their way through bring tears to my eyes with their substantial rawness. 

wow. that was a lot. it's good to get that out i guess. just things that i've been tumbling through my mind for a while now. i guess i'm not totally out of this teem angst phase. a writing class....hmmm. i'm gonna go check if any are available for fall quarter. night all. ~later
